"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0000","0","On March 8, the U.S. Senate passed the Lend-
Lease Act. The support for the U.S. has
increased in England and Holland.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0001","1","The United States will not fight in this war,
but we must serve as an armory for the nations
of democracy.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0002","2","The German battleship, Bismarck, was sunk in
the Atlantic on May 27.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0003","3","Superb! Our Royal Navy sunk Hitler's proud
Bismarck! The biggest threat in the Atlantic
has been destroyed.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0004","4","Although we lost the Bismarck, we still have
our sea wolves - the U-boats. Paralyze the
British sea transport and starve them.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0005","5","On June 22, the Third Reich breached the non-
aggression pact with Moscow and launched the
Barbarossa Operation to embark on the invasion
of the USSR.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0006","6","I declare the launch of the Barbarossa
Operation! With blitzkrieg by our Panzer,
Moscow will surrender before winter.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0007","7","My fellow citizens! We must stand up and
fight for our mother country! We must not let
invaders take a single grain of wheat or a drop
of gasoline!","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0008","8","On July 28, the Japanese army began occupying
Southern Indochina.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0009","9","The German-controlled French government has
accepted our demand to occupy Indochina. This
will secure us a foothold to the south.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0010","10","In response on the Japanese aggression in
French Indochina, the U.S. government froze all
Japanese assets in the U.S. The Japanese product-
ivity has dropped by 10%.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0011","11","The Japanese are disturbing peace in Asia by
imposing a selfish rationale. To stop their
aggression, we will have to take sanctions
against them.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0012","12","The U.S. imposed an oil embargo against Japan.
The Japanese productivity has dropped by 10%.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0013","13","As long as Japan maintains its armed diplo-
macy, we won't be able to continue the peace
conferences.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0014","14","Our fuel supply will last for only one more
year. We must quickly decide whether we'll fall
with or without fighting.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0015","15","The Japanese government has concluded that war
is inevitable unless there is a breakthrough in
the negotiations with the U.S. by early October.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0016","16","Mainland China is the lifeline of our army.
It's absolutely impossible to accept America's
demand for our complete withdrawal. I'm afraid
war is inevitable.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0017","17","The negotiation with Japan is coming to a
close. With our economic blockade pressing them
hard, it's a matter of time that they'll give in
to us.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0018","18","The Ministry of Foreign Affairs issued a
report on the statements from foreign leaders.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0019","19","We welcome Japan's diplomatic efforts. Depend-
ing on the circumstances, we may approve Japan's
interest in the Pacific.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0020","20","Our country has no intention to intervene
in the political and military affairs in the
Pacific. We will maintain neutrality.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0021","21","The United States is our comrade and the only
major power capable of overturning Fascism.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0022","22","I welcome Japan's diplomatic efforts. If we
can regain our land from the Germans, we will
not hesitate to support Japan.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0023","23","We will stand neutral regarding the conflicts
in the Pacific. We have no intention to make
political and military interventions.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0024","24","The United States is a symbol of freedom. Only
the United States will be able to restore the
Dutch land now occupied by the Germans.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0025","25","It's time to end the conflict with the
Japanese. If they support our rights and
interests, why not work with them for the
development of Asia!","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0026","26","We condemn the aggression of Imperial Japan.
If the United States are to stop them, we will
give our support.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0027","27","Amid the fight against the Germans, we do not
wish to provoke the Japanese and their army in
Manchuria. We value friendly relations with
Japan.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0028","28","Amid the fight against the Germans, we can't
afford to spread our forces to the Far East. We
will stand neutral for the time being.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0029","29","We are struggling against the Germans. We ask
the U.S. to open the second front and press
Germany.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0030","30","Japan is an important friend as well as a
former ally in the Tripartite Pact. I urge Japan
to declare war against the British and the
Russians as soon as possible.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0031","31","The goal of Germany is the unification of
Europe. War in the Pacific is not our concern.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0032","32","It is not in our best interest to face the
U.S. military power in Europe. Depending on the
circumstances, we may choose to ally with the
U.S.","",""
"EVMSG.TK2","EVMSG.TK2:0033","33","The State Department issued a report on the
statements from foreign leaders.","",""
